{
  "texts": [
    "For example, the illustrated Softmax layer (Fig. 1) produces probabilities over an output vocabulary during a language translation task.",
    "In NLP problems, this vocabulary corresponds to the lexicon of a language such as English or French.",
    "Similarly, programming language code generation using transformers (Svyatkovskiy et al. 2020) employs the tokens of the programming language as vocabulary.",
    "Observe that vocabularies are neither compulsory nor necessarily composed of textual tokens.",
    "For example, the study in Bao et al. (2021) shows that patches of an original image are employed as visual tokens."
  ]
}